==English==

===Pronunciation===
* ra-khy-ya

===Noun===
'''rakija'''
# Strong alchool drink made from fruit. In English closest equivqlent is "whiskey".  "Rakija" is general name for short and strong drinks made of fruit. Most frequent "rakija-s" are shlyvovica ("šljivovica", made of plum, lozovacha "lozovača", made of grapes' leftovers, yabukovacha "jabukovača", made of apple, and so on).  The name used mostly in Serbia, Croatia and Bosnia.  [[Serbian whishey]]

===Verb===
'''rakija'''
# In Serbian (Croatian/Bosnian) most frequent verb is "rakijati", which means to drink the beverage and got drunk.